<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-06-11T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-06-11T08:00:00-05:00" n="325" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/2428: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Arica</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Von
                                    Tresckow</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-11T09:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 11,
                                        1926—9 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>For Lassiter. Resolution which you have offered has aroused very bitter
                            feeling in Chilean Embassy here. They feel that it is unwarranted public
                            indictment of Chile and that honor will require her to break off
                            negotiations and possibly to break off relations with the United States.
                            If Chilean Commissioner proposes any possible solution or any compromise
                            arrangement by which passage of resolution would be avoided, please try
                            to adjourn action and cable us immediately.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>